{"/service/ndnp/dlc/batch_dlc_neptunian_ver01/data/sn83045462/00280657815/1910110601/0158.xml":{"full_text":"The World\nWashii\nSTOCK VALUES'GAIN\nHalt in Upward Movement\nOnly a Temporary One.\nMONEY ALARM IS ALLAYED\nLoan Secured in France Less Onerous\nThan Supposed.\nTRADE REVIEWS ENCOURAGE\nImpression Prevails that More Active\nBusiness Only Awaits Casting\nof Tuesday's Ballots.\n\nNEW YORK, November The speculative\nforce In the stock market renewed\nthe contest today for a higher range of\nprices. The reactionary tendency which\ndeveloped late yesterday was checked by\nthe authoritative statement from President\nBrown of the New York Central,\nontradirtlng the rumor that a sale of a\nlarge short-term note issue of that comnone\nwoe in *?oni <*m nl at inn That nimrtl*\nwas largely responsible for the sharp relapse\nin price* which occurred yesterday.\nPresident Itrewu's explicit, assertion\nthat the ?m.Oro.OC?> Michigan t'entra! note\nissue placed in Paris had cost that company\nbut per cent net served to correct\nrejMirts of an onerous interest rate\nwhich Itad been exacted for that financ- J\ning.\nDiscounting Tuesday*s Election.\nRelieved of litis depressing influence,\nthe speculation again set about discounting\nthe favorable conditions expected to\nfollow the passing of the elections. The\ntone of mercantile reviews fostered the\nimpression thai business activities were\nwaiting fcfr relief from the unsettlement I\nof political unrest in common with\nfinancial markets. The actual movement\nof the market was held in restraint by\nthe consideration of how much had been\nalready accomplished by the advance in\nprices in anticipating possible improvement\nin business and industry.\nTiic call money market Saturday at the\nstock exchange is merely nominal, as\nmans made Friday carry over until Monda>.\nThe tone of the time loan market\nwas called decidedly strong and more\nactive.\nThe foreign exchange market weakened\nsharply, and this was believed to reflect\nthe negotiation cf additional bankers'\niinnni... Kills in thp Paris and I.ondon\nmarkets. Tito private discount rate in\nl<ondofi moved toward further recovery,\ngiving evidence that the Bank of Kngland\nwas as.dn securing control and making\nits own rate effective in that market.\nBanks Lose in Cash.\nThe actual cash holdings of the' hanks\ndecreased here more than $6,500,000, in- j\nstead of the estimated $3,00O,tkX). The\nshipments-of gold late last week to Can-I\n:ida are believed not to have appeared in\nlast week's estimates. The actual surplus\nis reduced t?? $o,7?.l.0(l(> and the excess\nof loans over deposits is again broad- j1\nned.\nThe stock market closed easy under j\n'he influence of profit-taking sales.\nBonds were steady. Total sales par\nvalue, S1.0P7.n00.\nI'nited States, bonds are unchanged on\ncall from last week.\na\nClosing Stock List.\nSale* Cloa'f\nUigb. Low. bid.\n\\XW YORK. November 5.\nAllls-Chalmcr* pfd .14\nAmalgam*led Copper 71% 7i?4 741'\nAmerican Agricultural 47% 47% 47\nAmericau Iteet Sugar 38% 38% 38%\nAmerican Can 10% lo in i\nAmerican Car A Foundry 851., ,V>\nAmericau'otton Oil 67% 67% 67%\nAmer Hide A Leather pfd 155% 03^\nAmerican Jee Securities j9\nAmerican Linseed 12\nAmerican locomotive j. 41,\nAmer. Sraelllng A Refining 82% gia. gjrAmer.\nSmelting A Uetlniog pfd. 106% 106 106 i\nAmerican Steel Foundry 47% 47% 4710\nAmerican Sugar Refning 118%\nAmerican Tel. A Tel 142% 142% 142%\nAmerican Tobacco pfd 06% 96% ft',%\nAmericau Woolen 33%\nAnaconda Mining Co 42>s\nAtchison 104% 104% 104%\nAtchison pfd 101%\nAtlantic Coast Line U?\nBaltimore A Ohio 108%\nBethlehem Steel 32 31% 31% 1\nBrooklyn Rapid Transit 78% 77% 77% i\nWnadiau Pacific 108% 198 198'\nr entral Leather 35% 35% 35%\nCentral Leather pfd 105%'\nCentral of New- Jersey ^>sf, I\nheaapeakc A Ohio 84% 81% k4 I\nChicago 4 Alton 42\nhies go Great Western 24%\n^hlcago Great Western pfd.... 4g\nhioago 4 North Western 148%\nChicago. Mil. St. Paul 12?<% 125% 126%\nC.. C., C, 