70\nI nlted State* Rubber P~ :tt 36%\nI'nited States Steel 80% 80% 81\nI nited States Steel pfd 118\nt tsh Copper fai% 56% 66%\nVirginia-Carolina Chemical 64% 64% 64%\nWabash 18% 1H% 18\nW abash pfd 38', 38% 38-%\nWestern Maryland 47% 47% 47%:\nW'estingbouse Electric 73% 73% 73% j\nWestern Lniou 73 73 72%\nWheeling 4 Lake Erie 6\nTotal sales for the day. 279.1160 shares.\nManchester Cloth Market.\nMANCHESTER, November 5.?Business\nin the clot it market during the week was\nif fair dimensions and confined principally\n10 the home trade. China and NIedi-I\nterranean markets at firm prices. The\nIndian demand was checked by the holiday*.\nYarns were steadily maintained with a\nbetter trade in American descriptions,\nespecially medium fine sorts.\n3f Finance ar\nlgton; New Y\nNew York Bonds.\nNEW YORK. November 5.\nC. 8. ref. 2s, registered 94\nIT. S. ref. 2s, coupou 100%\nU. S. 3s.reg 100%\nU. a. 3s. coupon 101*4\nU. S. 4s, reg 101%\nC. S. 4s. coupon 113\nAllis-Cbslmers 1st 3s 115Vj\nAmerican Agricultural 5a. *77\nAmerican Tel. it Tel. cr. 4a 102%\nAmerican Tobacco 4s 100\nAmerlrau Tobacco 3s 80%\nArmour 4%s 10K\nAtchison general 4s 9214\nAtchison ov. 4s 98%\nAtchison cr. 3s 107,a\nAtlantic Coast Line 1st 4s lOK*.\nBaltimore it Ohio 4s 93%\nBaltimore Ohio 3%s 9*%\nBaltimore Oblo S. W. 3%s 92V,\nBrooklyn Transit ct. 4s 90%\nCentral of Georgia 5s 83\"4\nCentral Leather 5s 'lOO's 1\nCentral It. R of N. J. gen. 5s 90%\nnesapcake ft unio sv..m -isxta\nChesapeake ft Ohio rot. 6s 102\nt3)lcago Alton 3%s 93%\nChicago, B. ft Qulncy Joint 4? *70\nChicago. B. ft Qiilncv general 4a 90%\nChicago. MU. ft St. P. gen. 3%s !>7Vi\n'Chicago. R. I. ft Rao. K. R. ool. 4a *92\nChicago, 11. I. ft Pao. By. rfg. 4s 74%\nColorado Industrial 5s SO\nColorado Midland 4s *78\nColorado ft Southern ref. e?t. 4%a 70\nDelaware ft Hudson cv. 4a 07\nDenver ft Rio Grande 4a 98%\nDenver ft Rio Grande ref. 5s 1)4*8\nDistillers'5s 0?\nErie prior lien 4s 76**\nErie general 4s *83%\nErie cv. 4s. series \"A\" 7